summary: Lore friendly with the exception that my water looks more like clean lake or salt water. Nothing but ENB 266 or later needed.Performance version cost only 10 fps at most. Compatible with all mods period. Great for immersion, realistic needs, and hunting. Magic looks vivid and believable.
descriptionHtml:
[size=3]                                                      [youtube]DYUXd87QRmk[/youtube]
[center][/center]
[center][b][i][color=#ff0000]A finished work. HAIL![/color][/i][/b][/center][/size][center][/center][size=5][center][/center][center][color=#ff0000]Features:[/color]
[color=#ff0000]Superior Color, and Shading Correction[/color]
[color=#ff0000]S-Curves[/color]
[color=#ff0000]Skylighting[/color]
[color=#ff0000]Sunrays[/color]
[color=#ff0000]Full water effects[/color]
[color=#ff0000]Hand set SMAA for smooth play-ability, image, and frame-rate[/color]
[color=#ff0000]Sunglare ( 2 and 3 of all series )[/color]
[color=#ff0000]Dithering ( on 3 and authors preference of all series)[/color]
[color=#ff0000]Dynamic DoF ( 3 only toggle-able with all others )[/color]
[color=#ff0000]High Definition Resolution Effect ( 3 only )  [/color]
[color=#ff0000]Toggle-able effects are off by default but include:[/color]
[color=#ff0000]SSAO[/color]
[color=#ff0000]Sharpening ( variables given below in orange )[/color]
[color=#ff0000]Lens effect[/color]

[color=#ff0000]WINTER KILLS has all effects listed above with added Sub-Surface Scattering and letterbox and some fine tuning.[/color]
[color=#ff0000] [/color]
[color=#ff0000]Note: All are toggle-able unless otherwise specified.[/color]
[color=#ff0000]3 will not break your PC for trying it if you want to see if it will run.[/color]
[color=#ff0000]If your frame rate is horrible then go to 2 or cut some effects out with the[/color]
[color=#ff0000]ENB Interface ( Shift+Enter ).[/color]
[color=#ff0000]Scroll wheel does not work inside enb interface. You must drag the side bar.[/color][/center]
[center]Feel Free to add your own lens, and DoF effects to this preset.
Take screenshots and post them, with acknowledgment of
where you got your different effects.[/center]
[center]The link below is an older Winter Kills
but still gives you a idea of how it looks.

 A new preset coming soon![/center]
[color=#ff0000][url=http://onedrive.live.com/redir?resid=C15C1F614DE83ABB!1136&authkey=!ADU0r9LHT-tg7Vc&ithint=video%2cmp4][center]WINTER KILLS Skyrim Intro Video[/center][/url][/color]

[/size][size=3][color=#6aa84f]INSTALL:[/color]
[color=#6aa84f]This preset requires enb version 266 or later. If you dont know how to install enb then just type enb in your browser find ENB for Graphics Modification and download the zip and extract it. You should find the install read me pretty easy.

Make sure to set up your ini files like Boris says to ( on the ENB site ) and[/color][color=#f1c232] I recommend changing FoV to 90 by going to the skyrim.ini and putting this line at the end of the [Display] list   fDefaultWorldFOV=90.0  and make the skyrim.ini read only[/color][color=#6aa84f] especially if you use WINTER KILLS [/color][color=#f1c232]in-game put it in first person and bring up the menu and it will change and stay until you change it again (if you dont like it delete the line and its back to normal).[/color][color=#6aa84f] After you get this accomplished just extract my preset to your desktop. You will see a folder named Skyrim. Double click it and copy then paste its contents into the same folder that has your TESV.exe in it overwrite if asked and your done. In game[/color][color=#00ff00] push SHIFT+ENTER and set[/color][color=#6aa84f] the [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anisotropic_filtering][b][font=Segoe UI Semibold][color=#00ff00]Anisotropic filtering[/color][/font][/b][/url] higher if your machine has the power. It[/color][color=#00ff00] is set to X4 by default except on Winter Kills and the other high-end presets[/color][color=#6aa84f].

[/color][/size]if you have a 32bit os then edit "ExpandSystemMemoryX64=true" to false in enb.local.ini
Also, if you experience stuttering then try switching "EnableCompression=true" to false.
[color=#dd7e6b]VideoMemorySizeMb=xxxx[/color] to really set this is a no brainer. There is allot of formula for this but, I can show you how to get the number that is actually
right for your setup. For Nvidia users:[color=#ff7700] Go to Nvidia control panel [/color]and go to the[color=#ff7700] "help" tab[/color] the top of the window. Click it and find [color=#ff7700]"System Information"[/color].
You should see a list. In that list there is a line that says [color=#ff7700]"Total Graphic Memory Available"[/color]  mine says 6124mb and I have a 2gb(dedicated) card. So, I put 6124 by VideoMemorySizeMb=. For ATI graphics I guess you could do the same thing but I don't know my way around those cards. Never used one. You can do it from the system.
Be sure to turn off Antialiasing, and Anisotropic filtering in your launcher.

[color=#ff7700]I recommend using no Ambient Occlusion if you are trying to squeeze out every ounce of performance. If you want it enabled just press shift+enter and put a check by it. Or if you have an Nvidia card try using it's AO found in the Nvidia control pannel instead. DON'T USE BOTH![/color]

Recommended mods in blue below.

[size=3]I hope you enjoy Norse ENB and please endorse if you like it!

Please upload any screenshots of Norse ENB, videos are welcome too

With a horn of mead: "Hail to those who have endorsed"

My specs are:

Asrock 990fx Extreme 3 Motherboard
AMD 4350 Black ( running stock 4.2ghz )
8gb ram@1866 ( Ripjawz )
GTX 760 2gb    Gigabyte Windforce X3[/size]

[size=4]

[/size][color=#ffff00][size=4]Compatible with all mods except "IMO" vivid clouds and smoke plugin. The textures are great but I didn't like the look of my nights afterwards. But, that's my opinion so, it is technically compatible.[/size]

[/color]
                                                        
[color=#cc0000][size=4]Differences Between Presets Explained:[/size][/color]

[size=4]All Presets that are self titled or have a 1 behind it is intended for smooth playthrough without a lack of eyecandy. A hit of barely 10 fps.

Presets that are marked 2 expand on the effects for a little bit of a performance cost ( mid level machines should do fine ).

The Presets marked as 3 are built to be cinematic and require a bit of horsepower.

Author's Preference is just that. It's the way I like to play it. Only effects that you could see in real life are used. A hit of 10-15 fps.

WINTER KILLS is Version 4. It is an extreme enb. Low end PC wont hardly get double digit frame-rate. The extra bloom version is stylistically like bloom found in The Witcher 1, and 2.

Asgardian is actually an extension of WK. It has slight tweaking to make it different and has the Fog and cloud shadows added in automatically. Making it hit harder than WK.

Neverending is a more colorful, and light balanced approach to Asgardian, and is now my personal favorite.

Lighting Option 2 is a change of the overall feel of Norse ENB. Basically adding a dirty scarier look.

[/size][color=#3c78d8][size=4]Recommended Mods:
This preset looks best with [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/4323/?]Realistic Lighting without post-processing[/url] 1.6b or 1.6b BAIN. Also[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/13531/?] URWL[/url] Normal lighting
with textures from Realistic lighting without post-processing is what I'm using now, though no lighting is necessary.
I would use [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/17609/?]Relighting Skyrim[/url] to fix the vanilla lighting ( fires that glow but no light on the surrounding area ).
ELFX or RLO if you like, but I use URWL triple pack normal version.
Climates of Tamriel or Skyrim Enhanced Weathers ( not a necessity )
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/37900/?]UNP BLESSED BODY- UNPB REDUX PROJECT[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/52322/?]WSCO - Occidental Vanilla Body[/url] with[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/36510/?] Superior Lore Friendly Hair[/url] merged with some[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/18717/?] Temptress face[/url] tint masks and eyes is what I'm using
Wearable lanterns
Wet and Cold + wet and cold ashes
Tamriel Reloaded
SMIM
Skyrim HD texture packs ( both )
Realistic  HD Mod Series ( all of that stuff )
SFO or[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/60220/?tab=2&navtag=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nexusmods.com%2Fskyrim%2Fajax%2Fmodfiles%2F%3Fid%3D60220&pUp=1] Verdant [/url]or Unbelievable Grass or Grass on steroids or Skyrealism Grass ( all are good )
Realistic Water Two
Slofs  [url=http://www.slofslair.co.uk/mods/155]Iridescent Greybeard Robes[/url]       [url=http://www.slofslair.co.uk/mods/156]Vampire Stuff[/url]    
Primitive Horse breeds
Cinematic Fire and FX

For Performance and stability I highly recommend :

Stable uGridsToLoad
SKSE ini pre-download for lazy users
Save game script cleaner
Safety Load
Optimizer Textures ( I have a good rig and still use this to "wash" my 4k and 8k textures to 2k )
BSA Browser ( If you want to seriously Improve performance use this. details below )

Just this little handful would make a dramatic difference.
For fun try: [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/4793/?tab=2&navtag=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nexusmods.com%2Fskyrim%2Fajax%2Fmodfiles%2F%3Fid%3D4793&pUp=1]Conan[/url] Outfits, skin, and face save-game! 

Also join [url=https://www.facebook.com/groups/789380087840853/?notif_t=group_purposes_change¬if_id=1459744007343404]The Elder Scrolls passion[/url] on Facebook for friendly interaction with others who love Elder Scrolls games!
[/size]
The next things I'm going to mention is going to take some time...

Install: Stable uGridsToLoad ( even if you use default uGrids this thing rocks! )
SKSE ini pre-download for lazy users
Safety Load

After that use the instructions below

Performance tweak for great frame-rate improvement (+30 and into the thousands by ENB's frame counter ) with no loss of quality:

Using BSA browser extract all textures from all BSA's in this order for proper overwriting: Skyrim textures, DB BSA, DG BSA, HF BSA, Official HR texture packs 1, 2, then 3. Then put your personally added textures into the textures folder that has all the official textures in it. Put them through the optimizer I mentioned above. I set mine for make mipmaps if none and resize 4X4 ( you might want to try larger as everyone's taste is different ) Then I set the preferred texture resolution to reduce anything above 2k to be reduced to 2k. Hit start. Grab a snicker's.

After a long wait you will have perfected textures. Put them into your Skyrim textures folder and overwrite when asked.
Now ( trust me you don't want to erase any of the BSA's ) go to your launcher and uncheck all official HR texture plug-ins. They are now obsolete.
[/color]
After all that work you will be very happy

[center][color=#b45f06][b][i][size=4]Be sure to check out the stunning images that have been posted
in images from users. Special Thanks to mobiusbelmont, EMS60, and stac016.[/size][/i][/b][/color][i][color=#3c78d8]
[/color][/i][/center][size=4][center][/center][/size][center][color=#b45f06]
******************************************************************************************************************************************************************************
[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/67401-0-1441394521.jpg[/img]
[/color]Lo, there do I see my father. 'Lo, there do I see...
My mother, and my sisters, and my brothers.
Lo, there do I see...
The line of my people...
Back to the beginning.
Lo, they do call to me.
They bid me take my place among them.
In the halls of Valhalla...
Where the brave...
May live...
...Forever.[/center]

files.changelogHtml:
Finalized the series by adding a final Extreme Cinema version. Even better descriptions. A final skyrim.ini tweak for optional use (Highly Recommended).
Did some fixing on some things that bugged me @Final Cut
made better changes to the lighting (someone has been telling me to do this for a while) -Fire mostly @Final Cut
Made the night more like vanilla. Almost like a Polar Night ( google it ). Two moons would be brighter than one @Final Cut
In general the Final Cut patch is a merge of all things considered realistic ( Norway as a muse ) with things that are very Skyrim specific
I have thought about going to my other files including WK original and putting in all the changes. But, some people might think to change the files I already got up would be erasing their preferred preset. Might do a new run of files
